<item>
            <title>[WFLY-2573] The batch subsystem does not marshall the configuration correct in some circumstances</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-2573</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the batch subsystem is created, i.e. a new domain profile, the configuration is not applied correct.&lt;br/&gt;
It look like that it is partially applied &apos;in memory&apos; but not persisted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The used commands are:&lt;br/&gt;
/profile=default-web/subsystem=batch:add()&lt;br/&gt;
/profile=default-web/subsystem=batch/thread-pool=batch:add(keepalive-time=&lt;/p&gt;
{time=100,unit=milliseconds}
&lt;p&gt;, &lt;br/&gt;
max-threads=10)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The commands are running without messages, but the domain.xml looks like this&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;subsystem xmlns=&quot;urn:jboss:domain:batch:1.0&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                 &amp;lt;job-repository&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                     &amp;lt;in-memory/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                 &amp;lt;/job-repository&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
             &amp;lt;/subsystem&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
