                                                                                                                                                                                                            <customfield id="customfield_12310183" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Steps to Reproduce</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>&lt;p&gt;I use a batch script to configure a domain ( &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/wfink/quickstart/blob/ejb-multi-server-transfer/ejb-multi-server/install-domain.cli&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/wfink/quickstart/blob/ejb-multi-server-transfer/ejb-multi-server/install-domain.cli&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
)&lt;br/&gt;
You can run that script with &quot;jboss-cli.sh -c --file=install-domain.cli&quot; &lt;br/&gt;
against a fresh copy of wildfly Beta2 (upstream)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The batch is running without messages, but the domain.xml looks like this&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;subsystem xmlns=&quot;urn:jboss:domain:batch:1.0&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                 &amp;lt;job-repository&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                     &amp;lt;in-memory/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                 &amp;lt;/job-repository&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
             &amp;lt;/subsystem&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The used commands are:&lt;br/&gt;
/profile=default-web/subsystem=batch:add()&lt;br/&gt;
/profile=default-web/subsystem=batch/thread-pool=batch:add(keepalive-time=&lt;/p&gt;
{time=100,unit=milliseconds}, &lt;br/&gt;
max-threads=10)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
So the thread-pool is missing in the domain.xml.&lt;br/&gt;
But if I try to tun the second command again (after the script) I get this:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;domain@localhost:9990 /&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
/profile=default-web/subsystem=batch/thread-pool=batch:add(keepalive-time={time=100,unit=milliseconds}
&lt;p&gt;, &lt;br/&gt;
max-threads=10)&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
     &quot;outcome&quot; =&amp;gt; &quot;failed&quot;,&lt;br/&gt;
     &quot;failure-description&quot; =&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;domain-failure-description&quot; =&amp;gt; 
&quot;JBAS014803: Duplicate resource [
     (\&quot;profile\&quot; =&amp;gt; \&quot;default-web\&quot;),
     (\&quot;subsystem\&quot; =&amp;gt; \&quot;batch\&quot;),
     (\&quot;thread-pool\&quot; =&amp;gt; \&quot;batch\&quot;)
]&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
     &quot;rolled-back&quot; =&amp;gt; true,&lt;br/&gt;
     &quot;response-headers&quot; =&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;process-state&quot; =&amp;gt; &quot;reload-required&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After the domain is restarted the same command will run successfully.&lt;/p&gt;</customfieldvalue>

